Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Trim the @butternut squash{1}, halve lengthways, then scoop out the seeds (peel
first if you prefer). Cut into 2cm chunks.

Pop the diced butternut onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{1%tbsp},
sprinkle over the @Central American style spice mix{1%sachet}, then season with
@salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to coat, then spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden and cooked through,
~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into
thin strips.

Cut the @ciabatta{1} into roughly 2cm chunks. Zest and halve the @lemon{1}.

When the squash has roasted for ~{10%minutes}, add the sliced pepper to the
same baking tray. Drizzle with oil, season with salt and pepper, then toss to
coat.

Return to the oven and roast for the remaining until the peppers are soft and
slightly charred, ~{15-18%minutes}.

While the veg roasts, pop the ciabatta onto another medium baking tray in a
single layer. Drizzle with oil, sprinkle over the @dried oregano{1%sachet},
then season with salt and pepper. Toss to coat well.

Bake the croutons on the middle shelf until golden, ~{8-10%minutes}, then
remove from the oven and set aside.

In the meantime, heat the oil in a medium #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

> See pantry for amount of oil.

Once hot, add the @diced chorizo{60%g} and fry until it starts to brown,
~{3-4%minutes}.

Once browned, carefully drain the oil from the chorizo into a large #bowl{} for
the dressing. Set the chorizo aside.

Squeeze the juice of the lemon into the bowl of chorizo oil.

Add a good pinch of lemon zest and @sugar{1%tsp} for the dressing. Season with
salt and pepper, then mix well.

When everything's ready, add the roasted butternut squash, pepper, croutons and
@baby leaf mix{50%g} to the dressing and toss well. Taste and season with more
salt and pepper if needed.

Share the warm salad between your serving bowls.

Crumble over the @Greek style salad cheese{50%g} and sprinkle over the chorizo
to finish.

Enjoy!